  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Marketing Intern",
  "description": "<p>The Marketing Intern supports the marketing team in executing day-to-day brand, content, and campaign initiatives. This role is designed for individuals who want real, hands-on exposure to how a brand is built — from social content and on-ground activations to data tracking and creative ideation.</p><p>You’ll work closely with the founders, gaining practical experience across digital marketing, content creation, and brand storytelling.<br /></p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><p><strong>a. Social Media & Content Support</strong></p><p><ul><li>Assist in creating content for FB, Instagram, TikTok, RED, and other platforms</li><li>Support photo/video shoots, BTS content, and simple editing (CapCut / Canva)</li><li>Help prepare captions, hashtags, and posting schedules</li><li>Ensure content aligns with brand tone and guidelines</li></ul></p><p><strong>b. Campaign & Activation Support</strong></p><p><ul><li>Assist in executing marketing campaigns, promotions, and collaborations</li><li>Support live events, pop-ups, and in-store activations when required</li><li>Help coordinate timelines, deliverables, and simple tracking sheets</li></ul></p><p><strong>c. Research & Idea Generation</strong></p><p><ul><li>Conduct basic market, trend, and competitor research</li><li>Monitor social media trends, viral formats, and content ideas</li><li>Propose content ideas and campaign concepts during team discussions</li></ul></p><p><strong>d. Data & Performance Tracking</strong></p><p><ul><li>Assist in tracking social media performance and campaign results</li><li>Compile weekly or monthly performance summaries</li><li>Help identify what content performs well and why</li></ul></p><p><strong>e. Administrative & Team Support</strong></p><p><ul><li>Maintain content folders, calendars, and simple reports</li><li>Support coordination with designers, videographers, or outlets</li><li>Assist the marketing team with ad-hoc tasks as needed</li></ul></p><h3><strong>Required Skills & Attributes</strong></h3><p><ul><li>Interest in marketing, branding, or content creation</li><li>Familiarity with Instagram, TikTok, and social platforms</li><li>Basic design or video editing skills (Canva / CapCut preferred)</li><li>Good time management and willingness to learn</li><li>Proactive, responsible, and able to take initiative</li><li>Comfortable working in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Willing to follow the founder travel to Malaysia Johor Bahru (one day trip only)</li></ul></p><h3><strong>Performance Expectations</strong></h3><p><ul><li>Consistent and timely support for marketing tasks</li><li>Willingness to learn, adapt, and improve</li><li>Attention to detail and accountability for assigned work</li><li>Positive attitude and teamwork</li></ul></p>",
